  cat << EOF

${BOLD}kit-workspace v${VERSION}${NC}
Multi-repo agent orchestration toolkit.

${BOLD}USAGE${NC}
  kit-workspace <command> [options]

${BOLD}COMMANDS${NC}
  init
      Initialise ~/.kit-workspace/ and create a default workspace.json.

  session start <app-or-project> <name> "<description>" [--mode 1|2|3|4]
      Start a session against an app or project. No agent config needed.

  session list
      List all sessions with status and type (alias: sessions).

  session merge <id>
      Merge a completed session and infer its type from commits.

  add-project <name> <path> [--driver petfi-kit|generic]
      Register a project. Default driver: generic.

  list-projects
      List all registered projects with their path and driver.

  add-app <name> <project> [project...]
      Group projects under a named app (e.g. nogal = nomades-webapp + nomades-bff).

  list-apps
      List all app groups.

  new [--name <name>] [--from-template]
      Interactive wizard to create a new job.json.
      --from-template  Copy the single-repo template instead of wizard.

  refine <job.json> [output.json]
      Run a planner agent (product-owner/planner/architect) to elaborate the job
      spec before implementation. Outputs job-refined.json for review.

  run <job.json> [--mode 1|2|3|4] [--dry-run] [--refine]
      Execute a job. job.json can be a path or a name in ~/.kit-workspace/jobs/.
      --mode 1   Supervised (tmux, you watch)
      --mode 2   Semi-auto (tmux, auto-accept)
      --mode 3   Fire & Forget (headless)
      --mode 4   Agent Teams (headless, parallel)
      --dry-run  Print the execution plan without running.
      --refine   Refine the spec with a planner agent before running.

  status [<job-id>]
      Without job-id: one-liner status for all jobs.
      With job-id: detailed status for that job.

  dashboard
      Render a full visual table of all jobs.

  logs <job-id> [--role <role>] [--follow]
      Tail log output for a job. --role targets a specific agent log.
      --follow  Stream updates (tail -f).

  merge <job-id>
      Rebase each feature branch onto main, merge, push, and remove the worktree.
      Conflicts are resolved automatically by a Claude agent.
      Records the job in history.json and commits it.

  history
      List all merged features from history.json.

  stop <job-id>
      Send SIGTERM to all agent processes and clean up worktrees.

  clean [--all] [--job <job-id>]
      Remove state for completed/failed jobs.
      --all         Remove all state (prompts for confirmation).
      --job <id>    Remove state for a specific job.

  doctor
      Check dependencies and configuration.

  version
      Print the version string.

  help
      Show this message.

${BOLD}EXAMPLES${NC}
